'''Material flow''' is the description of the transportation of raw materials, pre-fabricates, parts, components, integrated objects and final products as a flow of entities. The term applies mainly to advanced modeling of [[supply chain management]].
As industrial material flow can easily become very complex, several different specialized simulation tools have been developed for complex systems. Typical tools are: * [[AnyLogic]] * AutoMod for logistics systems * [[Plant Simulation]] for production system
